# media-aggregator
You are building a production-ready backend service called "Media Aggregator".

The project is part of a larger ecosystem consisting of:

1. Radio Core
   - Media engine
   - Streaming backend
   - Playback API
   - Storage abstraction
   - AI orchestration

2. Listen
   - Public audio player
   - On-demand playback
   - Playlists and user experience

3. Radio Uppsala
   - Editorial/public media site

The Media Aggregator is responsible for:

- ingesting external media and metadata
- normalizing data
- enriching metadata
- processing AI workflows
- syncing content into Radio Core
- federation between external platforms and internal systems

The architecture must be modern, modular, Docker-ready and future Kubernetes-compatible.

